description "2 words, 9 letters. Puzzles like this are tricky because I want to get the image down, and filling in the bottom bits would've made things easier but detracted from what I wanted to try. And the thing is, I liked the logic at play here, so if people but I don't want to waste people's time with something tougher than they want to deal with. Hence the suggestion in the title. Ironic that simple ideas sometimes make for tough puzzles. Also interesting that symmetry provides shortcuts for a guess-the-palindrome puzzle."
